Schematic of the planar and proposed light-trapping structures. The width of the simulated unit cell is 350 nm. The curved Au in (c,e) is a semi-circle with a radius of 100 nm. All other convex nanostructures are semi-ellipses. The curved HTL in (c,e) has a minor radius of 100 nm and a major radius of 110 nm, the curved perovskite has a minor radius of 100 nm and a major radius of 120 nm, the curved ETL has a minor radius of 110 nm and major radius of 150 nm, and the curved ITO has a minor radius of 135 nm and major radius of 165 nm.Fig. 4
